Figure 15 and Table 4 show the results for reopening with the US versus the United Kingdom(UK). We estimate that the cumulative cases will differ by 53,825 people if we resume 100% with the US as opposed to remain at current traffic. However, the cumulative cases will differ by 1264 for the UK. The impact of resuming flights with the UK is negligible compared to that of US. This can be explained by the fact that half of Canada’s international flights are coming from the US and that UK has far lower positive rate than the US.Table 4
